The paper deals with signal quantization and compression techniques in a cloud radio access network (C-RAN) system, which involves wireless communication and network optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data compression and transmission. The paper also involves network optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions orthogonal frequency division multiple access (OFDMA) and wireless power control, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
